Fulsungi is a quaint suburb located in the state of Uttarakhand. The National Highways 74 and 87 pass along the two borders of this area thus making commuting easy for its residents. Rudrapur City Railway Station is a major junction that can be reached conveniently via Kashipur Bypass Road. Pantnagar and Mahendranagar Airport is at short driving distance from Fulsungi. Esther Industries Ltd. and Laxmi Stone Industries are some of the well known industries close to this area thus attracting many working professionals to settle in and around this locale. Columbus Public School, Bhartiyam International School and Jaycees Public School are some of the famous schools in the vicinity. Amrapali Institute and SVM Inter College are some of the popular colleges nearby. The area also has prominent healthcare centres, shopping areas, eatery joints and other entertainment avenues. The presence of basic establishments has transformed this locale as one of the most preferred residential areas of Uttarakhand. Also the presence of famous Shiv Mandir of Gangapur at a short distance bestows divine importance as well to this suburb.

MOUNTAIN BROOK HOMES is a group of 6 cottages on the bank of a major steam in village Chamfi near Bhimtal in Dist. Nainital. Mountain and water is a remarkable combination & the area is famous for it's mountains, lakes and cottages. As you go towards Mukhteshwar from Bhimtal, you encounter an iron bridge at about 8 km down the road. This road is also a bird watchers trail.     When you arrive at the bridge, ask the pertinent question from the toll guy... Jain Saheb ke cottage kahaan hain ... You will get succinct directions. Take your car right down to the site. The breeze is perfect here and vistas very fine.    There are 2 types of cottages on offer 2/4-BHK. Sizes are generous. Being close to the river, there is a perennial source of water. The homes are close to a village, so there isn't a sense of being alone in the hills. The site is motor-able and there is a common parking for 8 cars.
